            "plan": "\n## Overview\n\nThree categories of work: (1) fill UI consistency gaps, (2) extract duplicated resolve+store logic, (3) add missing test coverage for the decoupled pattern. Following TDD: write tests first that assert new decoupled behavior, verify they fail against old logic, then implement.\n\n---\n\n## 1. Test Gaps to Fill (TDD -- write these first)\n\n### 1a. `resolveInteractionSettings.test.ts` -- Missing edge case\n\n**Gap:** No test for \"only `autonomyLevel` provided, no `interactionMode`\" -- this exercises the fallback path for `interactionMode`.\n\n```ts\nit('uses fallback interactionMode when only autonomyLevel is provided', () => {\n  const result = resolveInteractionSettings({\n    autonomyLevel: AutonomyLevel.High,\n    fallback: { interactionMode: DroidInteractionMode.Auto, autonomyLevel: AutonomyLevel.Off },\n  });\n  expect(result).toEqual({\n    interactionMode: DroidInteractionMode.Auto, // from fallback\n    autonomyLevel: AutonomyLevel.High,           // from explicit\n  });\n});\n```\n\n**Expectation:** This should pass immediately (existing logic handles it). This is a coverage gap, not a behavior gap.\n\n### 1b. `useActiveSessionSettings.test.ts` -- Missing decoupled initialization and update tests\n\n**Gaps identified:**\n- No test initializing with decoupled `interactionMode` + `autonomyLevel` in `initialSettings` (all existing tests use legacy `autonomyMode: AutonomyMode.Normal`)\n- No test for `updateInteractionSettings` (the new method) -- only `updateAutonomyMode` is tested\n- No test asserting `currentInteractionMode` and `currentAutonomyLevel` exposed state\n- `initializeFromSessionManager` test checks `currentAutonomyMode` but never checks `currentInteractionMode` or `currentAutonomyLevel`\n\n**New tests to add:**\n\n```ts\n// Initial state\nit('should initialize with decoupled interactionMode and autonomyLevel from initialSettings', () => {\n  // Pass interactionMode: Spec, autonomyLevel: High\n  // Assert cur